# IH design spec — always in context

This playground treats **`design-sandbox/design.md`** as the **canonical written** Included Health design-system reference for principles, foundations, tokens, components, patterns, and agent-facing rules.

**Included file (keep in Agent context):**

@design-sandbox/design.md

**How to use it**

- Prefer **`design.md`** over memory for anything covered there (colors, type, spacing, components, messaging patterns, etc.).
- Use **Figma MCP** / **ih-figma-ds-visual-refs** when you need Anatomy visuals, screenshots, variants, or detail **not** spelled out in **`design.md`**.
- Layer **`design-sandbox/app-visual-language.md`** and **`design-sandbox/personas/`** for product-specific feel and audience; do not duplicate long DS prose from **`design.md`** into those files.
- If **`design.md`** and Figma appear to conflict, call it out and default to the **written** rule in **`design.md`** unless the user resolves otherwise.
